In the experiments described in the manuscript, electron-spin resonance and nuclear magnetic resonance were registered as a change in the mechanical resonance frequency of a cantilever.
Thermo-mechanical position fluctuations place a fundamental limit on how small a cantilever frequency shift can be measured in a given averaging time \cite{Albrecht1991jan,Obukhov2007feb,Yazdanian2008jun,Dwyer2015jan}.
